      <head>Karl Rothberger</head>
      <div>
        <p>Son of <ref cRef="rothberger_alfred">Alfred Rothberger</ref> and his wife <ref
            cRef="rothberger_hilda">Hilda</ref>, long-time close friends of Heinrich and Jeanette
          Schenker. In a letter of 1938 to UE, Jeanette states that she has authorized Karl
          Rothberger as translator of <title level="m">Harmonielehre</title> (UEA [5], May 30).</p>

        <p>Letters from Karl Rothberger to the Schenkers are preserved in the file of correspondence
          from Hilda Rothberger as OJ 13/31 (between 1929 and 1938). It was Karl who informed the
          Schenkers on May 24, 1932 of his father's death (OJ 4/5, p. 3732). </p>

      </div>
